<div class="aap-about-v1">
  <section class="aap-section">
    <div class="aap-wrap aap-grid-2">
      <div>
        <span class="aap-kicker">About AdvanceAPractice</span>
        <h1>Portland-rooted healthcare operations support built for practices far beyond one local market.</h1>
        <p>AdvanceAPractice is a healthcare operations, billing, credentialing, workflow, and practical AI implementation partner for growing practices that need more structure, better visibility, and stronger follow-through behind the business side of care.</p>
        <p>The company is especially credible in behavioral health, including therapy, psychiatry, counseling, psychology, and PMHNP practice operations, while also supporting broader outpatient medical practices that need cleaner revenue-cycle workflows, credentialing support, and more organized systems.</p>
        <p>What makes AdvanceAPractice different is that the work is not framed as generic consulting, cheap outsourced billing, or hype-driven AI. The approach is implementation-led, EHR-agnostic where workable, and built around how practices actually operate day to day.</p>

        <div class="aap-actions">
          <a class="aap-btn primary" href="/contact-us/">Start the Conversation</a>
          <a class="aap-btn secondary" href="mailto:info@advanceapractice.com">Email AdvanceAPractice</a>
        </div>

        <div class="aap-proof">
          <div class="aap-proof-card">
            <strong>Portland-rooted credibility</strong>
            <span>Based in Portland, supporting practices across Oregon, Washington, and throughout the U.S.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="aap-proof-card">
            <strong>Behavioral health strength</strong>
            <span>Strong fit for therapy groups, psychiatry practices, PMHNP teams, and growing behavioral health organizations.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="aap-proof-card">
            <strong>Implementation-focused</strong>
            <span>Built around workflow clarity, staff adoption, operational follow-through, and current-system fit.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="aap-visual">
        <img src="https://advanceapractice.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/dji_fly_20211031_131926_111_1661050875067_photo-1-scaled.webp" alt="Pacific Northwest aerial image representing Portland-rooted healthcare operations support">
        <div class="aap-visual-note">
          <strong>Local credibility, broader reach</strong>
          <span>AdvanceAPractice is rooted in Portland but structured to support healthcare teams well beyond one local market.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="aap-section aap-sky">
    <div class="aap-wrap aap-grid-2" style="align-items:center; gap:60px;">
      <div style="text-align:center;">
        <img
          src="https://advanceapractice.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/ryan-berg-advanceapractice.png"
          alt="Ryan Berg, Founder of AdvanceAPractice"
          style="width:220px; height:220px; object-fit:cover; border-radius:50%; box-shadow:var(--aap-shadow-lg); border:4px solid rgba(16,40,65,.08);"
        />
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="aap-kicker">About the Founder</span>
        <h2>Ryan Berg</h2>
        <p style="font-size:0.95rem; color:var(--aap-slate); margin-bottom:1.5rem; font-style:italic;">Founder, AdvanceAPractice &mdash; Portland, OR</p>
        <p>Ryan has spent 16 years inside the operational and financial side of healthcare &mdash; starting in collections and denial management at OHSU, building through account management and EHR implementation across national outpatient practices, and eventually leading the operational consolidation and revenue growth of a multi-state behavioral health group from $2M to $6M in annual revenue.</p>
        <p>The work at AdvanceAPractice is a direct extension of that background. It stays close to the real pressure points: claim flow, provider readiness, denial patterns, system use, and the handoffs that tend to break down under volume.</p>
        <p>He has worked across a wide range of practice types &mdash; psychiatry, PMHNP, therapy, counseling, PT, OT, and speech pathology &mdash; and with EHR and PM systems including AdvancedMD, SimplePractice, Athena, Valant, TherapyNotes, and EPIC, among others.</p>
        <p>The point is not to add another layer of advice. It is to get close enough to the actual operating reality that the next step is usable.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="aap-section aap-sand">
    <div class="aap-wrap">
      <span class="aap-kicker">What This Company Is</span>
      <h2>A more practical model for healthcare support.</h2>
      <div class="aap-grid-3">
        <div class="aap-card">
          <h3>Healthcare operations partner</h3>
          <p>AdvanceAPractice helps practices improve workflow design, operational visibility, admin follow-through, and the systems that support smoother growth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="aap-card">
          <h3>Revenue-aware implementation partner</h3>
          <p>Billing, denials, credentialing, intake, and documentation are treated as connected workflows instead of siloed tasks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="aap-card">
          <h3>Practical AI support model</h3>
          <p>Technology is used carefully where it reduces friction, improves visibility, and supports better operations without reckless automation claims.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="aap-section aap-forest">
    <div class="aap-wrap aap-grid-2">
      <div>
        <span class="aap-kicker">How The Work Is Approached</span>
        <h2>Built around real healthcare operations, not abstract strategy.</h2>
        <p>AdvanceAPractice works from the operational reality of the practice first: how information moves, where delays happen, where staff are overloaded, where revenue is leaking, and where workflows are creating avoidable friction.</p>
        <p>That is why the company’s work often spans multiple connected areas, including <a href="/mental-health-billing/">mental health billing services</a>, <a href="/medical-billing/">medical billing services</a>, <a href="/credentialing-accelerator/">provider credentialing services</a>, <a href="/ai-documentation/">AI documentation support</a>, <a href="/ai-revenue-cycle/">AI revenue cycle support</a>, and <a href="/practice-automation-consulting/">practice automation consulting for healthcare</a>.</p>
        <p>The goal is not to make the practice more complicated. The goal is to help current systems work better, reduce administrative burden, improve follow-through, and create a cleaner foundation for growth.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="aap-panel">
        <div class="aap-panel-inner">
          <h3>Why practices choose AdvanceAPractice</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Strong behavioral health and outpatient workflow credibility</li>
            <li>EHR-agnostic philosophy where workable</li>
            <li>Remote-first support with in-person support when appropriate</li>
            <li>Operations-aware and revenue-aware decision-making</li>
            <li>Implementation focus instead of vague recommendation-heavy consulting</li>
            <li>Practical AI positioned with review, control, and workflow discipline</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="aap-section aap-sea">
    <div class="aap-wrap aap-grid-2">
      <div>
        <span class="aap-kicker">Leadership & Experience</span>
        <h2>Experienced leadership without turning the page into founder mythology.</h2>
        <p>AdvanceAPractice was founded by Ryan Berg and built from real healthcare administrative, operational, and revenue-cycle experience. That background matters because healthcare practices do not need surface-level business advice. They need support from someone who understands how billing, staffing, provider growth, onboarding, workflows, reimbursement, and practice operations actually affect one another.</p>
        <p>The company’s experience is especially relevant for independent practices and growing groups that need more than task completion. They need better systems, better visibility, and better execution behind the scenes.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="aap-quote">
          <blockquote>“Ryan’s unique ability to have executive and business-like vision as well as possess the details of daily operations has been and continues to be crucial in delivering, serving, and supporting our patients, employees, and contractors.”</blockquote>
          <div class="aap-attrib">
            <strong>Tim Perez, PMHNP-BC</strong>
            Co-founder, ValueCore Mental Health
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="aap-section">
    <div class="aap-wrap">
      <div class="aap-cta">
        <span class="aap-kicker">Next Step</span>
        <h2>Need a healthcare operations partner that understands billing, workflow, credentialing, and practical implementation?</h2>
        <p>If your practice is dealing with administrative overload, denial-heavy workflows, credentialing drag, documentation burden, or growth that is exposing weak systems, AdvanceAPractice is built to help create a cleaner and more dependable operating model.</p>
        <div class="aap-actions">
          <a class="aap-btn primary" href="/contact-us/">Start the Conversation</a>
          <a class="aap-btn secondary" href="/resources/">Explore Resources</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
